e the\n21cm transition in neutral hydrogen prior to reionization, and demonstrate that\nthese experiments will be extremely useful in improving sensitivity to masses\nnear $\\sim 10^{-14}$ eV, potentially by several orders of magnitude. Finally,\nwe discuss implications for reionization, early star formation, and late-time\n$y$-type spectral distortions, and show that probes which are inherently\nsensitive to the inhomogeneous state of the Universe could resolve signatures\nunique to the light dark photon...\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Mar 2020 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 22 Jun 2020 07:58:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-15"}
